      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The Dunn camp has an absolute stranglehold on this contest. ALLEZE (2) is yet to taste defeat. He was a strong debut winner when well backed here on debut back in October, then returned a winner at Grafton last month. Progressive type that can keep the ball rolling. TOO HOT TO TORQUE (4) couldn't quite live up to market expectations when resuming at Ballina but never stopped trying to the line. Will appreciate the anticipated tempo and should be sling-shotting off their backs late. LOVECATS (6) dug deep when challenged first-up at the Sunshine Coast, sticking her head out to score. Strips fitter second-up and is sure to be prominent again, though may be vulnerable late. STORM MERCHANT (5) showed good tactical speed when resuming at Grafton but tired late in the piece, and was slow to recover. Strips fitter second-up and is sure to be giving himself every chance again up on speed. RUPESTRIS (7) is another progressive type for the Dunn camp that resumes. Can also make a case.",
